TITLE: Implementing Custom Filter Resolver
DESCRIPTION: Implementation of the custom isCompleted filter resolver in Go. It adds a predicate to filter completed or not completed todos based on the input.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ent/ent/blob/master/doc/md/tutorial-todo-gql-filter-input.md#2025-04-22_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
func (r *todoWhereInputResolver) IsCompleted(ctx context.Context, obj *ent.TodoWhereInput, data *bool) error {
	if obj == nil || data == nil {
		return nil
	}
	if *data {
		obj.AddPredicates(todo.StatusEQ(todo.StatusCompleted))
	} else {
		obj.AddPredicates(todo.StatusNEQ(todo.StatusCompleted))
	}
	return nil
}
```

