TITLE: Appending Values to JSON Arrays in PostgreSQL
DESCRIPTION: This SQL snippet demonstrates how to atomically append a value to a JSON array in PostgreSQL, handling edge cases where the field might not exist or be null.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ent/ent/blob/master/doc/website/blog/2022-10-10-json-append.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
UPDATE "t" SET "c" = CASE
WHEN
    (("c"->'a')::jsonb IS NULL
    OR ("c"->'a')::jsonb = 'null'::jsonb)
THEN
    jsonb_set("c", '{a}', 'new_val', true)
ELSE
    jsonb_set("c", '{a}', "c"->'a' || 'new_val', true)
END
