TITLE: Applying Schema with Atlas Go SDK
DESCRIPTION: Go code snippet demonstrating how to apply schema changes using the Atlas Go SDK.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ent/ent/blob/master/doc/md/migration/functional-indexes.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: Go
CODE:
```
ac, err := atlasexec.NewClient(".", "atlas")
if err != nil {
	log.Fatalf("failed to initialize client: %w", err)
}
// Automatically update the database with the desired schema.
// Another option, is to use 'migrate apply' or 'schema apply' manually.
if _, err := ac.SchemaApply(ctx, &atlasexec.SchemaApplyParams{
	Env: "local",
	URL: "postgres://postgres:pass@localhost:5432/database?sslmode=disable",
	AutoApprove: true,
}); err != nil {
    log.Fatalf("failed to apply schema changes: %w", err)
}
```

